  "text": "Lipid A samples were prepared as described previously [CITATION_1] , with a slight modification. Bacteria were grown overnight in N-minimal media with 10 mM MgCl2, pH 7.7 at 37°C. Then, the cells were washed and diluted into N-minimal media with 10 mM MgCl2, pH 5.8 to be a final inoculum size of 10 4 cfu ml -1 . Sixty microlitres (60 spots of 1 ml diluted cells) of each strain was spotted onto an N-minimal pH 5.8 10 mM MgCl2 agarose plate containing 50 mM FeCl3 with the use of a multipoint inoculator (Sakuma Seisakusyo, Tokyo, Japan), followed by incubation at 37°C for 20 h. The cells were then harvested, washed, and suspended in 0.8 ml PBS, pH 7.4. Preparation of lipid A samples and MALDI-TOF mass spectrometry analyses of lipid A were performed in the negative ion mode on a Voyager DE STR mass spectrometer (PerSptive Biosystems) as described [CITATION_2] .",
